   "body" : "Introduce a smart pointer that provides a thread-safe access to any object by using an internal mutex which is acquired every time a method of the object is called and released afterwards. Also, provide a way to explicitly lock the object for scenarios where it has to be protected for longer, e.g. during multiple calls of its methods.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\nThreadSafePtr<std::unordered_map<int, int>> m{{3, 9}, {4, 16}};\r\n\r\n// This is thread-safe, a mutex is acquired before emplace() and\r\n// released afterwards.\r\nm->emplace(5, 25);\r\n\r\n{\r\n    auto m_locked = *m; // acquire the mutex\r\n\r\n    auto it = m_locked->find(5);\r\n    if (it != m_locked->end()) {\r\n        std::cout << it->second << std::endl;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    for (auto& [k, v] : m_locked) {\r\n        std::cout << k << \", \" << v << std::endl;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // the mutex is released when `m_locked` goes out of scope\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRemove the global mutex `g_maplocalhost_mutex` and use `ThreadSafePtr` instead of it.\r\n",
